</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utudamorf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tudamorf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/02 9:45:57 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27553.topic&index=34>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/lag999/rtfm.txt width=100 height=100></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why all the complaints about the new focus items?</span><hr size=1> Scirocco says:  <b><I>Every argument that can be made in support of the current approach to caster focus effects also applies to melee effects like haste. </b></i><br>
<br>
Not really.<br>
<br>
Melees <b>need</b> haste to be effective, since it gives them a 100% power boost (spell plus item).  The entire game has been balanced from the very beginning with haste in mind, and higher end encounters are designed to assume that the melees all have haste.<br>
<br>
Focus items are just icing on the cake for casters, stretching some of their abilities by about 10% on average.  The appropriate analogy would be to critical hits for melees, not haste.  Plus, a mage can always summon them for casters that don't have a permanent item.  Can a mage summon a 41% haste item for a melee?<br>
<br>
<b><i>Twinking would be limited by added a character level limit to each effect.</b></i><br>
<br>
Retroactively changing many items to be level-limited is a bad idea.  How would you like to log on suddenly and find you can no longer equip some of your items because some high level player was complaining that it should have a better effect?  Remember that these items are useful for a wide variety of players. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uscirocco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scirocco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>FAQ/Index Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/7/02 11:29:42 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27553.topic&index=35>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why all the complaints about the new focus items?</span><hr size=1> Casters are so far behind the curve, that anything, even 10%, is "needed."   Casters need the focus items one hell of a lot more than a melee needs haste right now.<br>
<br>
<b>Retroactively changing many items to be level-limited is a bad idea. </b><br>
<br>
Re-read my post.  I said nothing about making items level limited. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/bthedruidsgrove.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=araxx>Araxx</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/8/02 5:49:34 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27553.topic&index=36>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why all the complaints about the new focus items?</span><hr size=1> Hey Scirocco:<br>
I might have read your post wrong, but there have been arguments in favor of increasing an item's % effectiveness as you pass lvl 20 and 44, and removing the I, II, and III tag. Unless I've totally lost my ability to comprehend english... :P<br>
I totally agree we should not lose the effect of an item because we level, and the example of an FBSS not working after a warrior levels is very valid. Then again, just check out how farmed that item is and imagine some similar focus item...<br>
Personally I want caster balancing yesterday, and focus effects to go along with the appropriate item for the targetted class. But we also need to get better items with better focus effects, imo. Let the I tag mean 5%, II 10%, and III 15%, sure, that works fine, and it works like a normal item with 3, 5, or 10 wis on it, we'd be wanting that item as we are able to get it and level, but the wis isn't dropped once we reach lvl 44... to put an example we all have talked about. But there's something about this whole system which has me at a loss and I can't quite put my finger on. I think we're in for a surprise... And it had better be a good one. :P<br>
<br>
Ciao for now!<br>
