<br>
You only get higher percentages if you upgrade to the higher level items.  And given the amount of effort people go through to upgrade for a few points more of resistance, wis, mana, etc., I imagine that casters will similarly want to upgrade to get 5% to 20% more focus effect.<br>
<br>
If any high levels farm lower level items, it will be to sell the item to lower level players.  And that is EXACTLY the same thing that can happen under the current system. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umissfoxfyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Miss Foxfyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Administrator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/8/02 7:18:19 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27553.topic&index=38>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://gwynhyfar.homestead.com/files/hm9.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why all the complaints about the new focus items?</span><hr size=1> <i>the example of an FBSS not working after a warrior levels is very valid. Then again, just check out how farmed that item is and imagine some similar focus item...</i><br>
<br>
I am not even sure anymore that we can draw such parallels with melees. While it's true a haste item doesn't stop working as levels increase, upgrading to better haste items is a given. How many melees do you know are still using an FBSS? Because there are upgrades, no melee wants "old crap." Doesn't the existence of a higher focus on an item fit into this whole upgrade treadmill? :D<br>
<br>
Second, we do have existing items with permeffects. Perhaps there are not enough of these items overall. That's why focus items made sense, especially for the low-mid levels who won't/don't get FT items.<br>
<br>
<br>
<i>we'd be wanting that item as we are able to get it and level, but the wis isn't dropped once we reach lvl 44...</i><br>
<br>
Casters have always had to choose between situational gear. In fact, before the rampant abundance of wisdom items, you used to have to sacrifice day-to-day gear for resist gear, and your wisdom would take a toll and could drop by as many as 20 points. I know that I used to don 180 wisdom with resist gear on. Those just entering the "raid machine" and buying resist gear may still have to sacrifice wisdom or mana or both to make up for resists. <br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uscirocco.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Scirocco</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>FAQ/Index Moderator</span><br> <font color=#333399>(6/8/02 8:57:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovegeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=27553.topic&index=39>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Why all the complaints about the new focus items?</span><hr size=1> <b>I am not even sure anymore that we can draw such parallels with melees. While it's true a haste item doesn't stop working as levels increase, upgrading to better haste items is a given. How many melees do you know are still using an FBSS? Because there are upgrades, no melee wants "old crap." Doesn't the existence of a higher focus on an item fit into this whole upgrade treadmill? :D</b><br>
<br>
Sure we can draw the parallel.  And the existence of higher focus items is a given, since there are already high focus items in the game.  We just don't have enough of them.  But in the interim, doesn't it make sense that a level II spell haste item (like the NoS) should work equally well whether I am casting a level 44-60 spell as one below 44?<br>
<br>
Otherwise, your argument about how melee players upgrade haste is exactly my argument.  No caster is going to want "old crap" with level I or II effects if there are upgrades to level III with better stats available.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<b>Second, we do have existing items with permeffects. Perhaps there are not enough of these items overall. That's why focus items made sense, especially for the low-mid levels who won't/don't get FT items.</b><br>
<br>
I daresay a lot of high levels won't get more than a few FT items, if any.  Sure, items with permeffects make a lot of sense, as do focus items.  It's merely the implementation of the latter that many of us take issue with.<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<b>Casters have always had to choose between situational gear. In fact, before the rampant abundance of wisdom items, you used to have to sacrifice day-to-day gear for resist gear, and your wisdom would take a toll and could drop by as many as 20 points. I know that I used to don 180 wisdom with resist gear on. Those just entering the "raid machine" and buying resist gear may still have to sacrifice wisdom or mana or both to make up for resists. </b><br>
<br>
This also applies to melee, of course.  But since melee can get effects like haste without having to resort to "old crap," there's no reason to make casters resort to "old crap" for their focus effects, either.  It's also a double whammy...under the current system, casters have to use "old crap" for their caster effects, AND use lower level spells to get the benefit of the effects.   At least under my system, the simple tradeoff of going for "old crap" items to get a useful effect would be in place.  <br>
<br>
Sort of like a high level warrior forced to use a FBSS for the haste if no upgrade were available.  The parallel to the current caster situation is to force the tank to use a FS weapon with the FBSS to get the benefit of the haste.<br>
<br>
